# Differential co-batch negate (analysis sec 4.5 R9): one @differential
# message feeds both pred (Tag 0) and negated (Tag 1); one epoch carries
# both changes. Four keys, one per F-A mixed case.
#
# Batch 1 (setup): establish the pre-states each case flips FROM.
#   key 20: blk(20) present (case 2 will remove it while adding pr(20)).
#   key 30: pr(30,300) present, no blk (case 3 will remove pr, add blk(30));
#           out(30,300) is live here.
#   key 40: pr(40,400) present AND blk(40) present (case 4 removes both);
#           out(40,400) absent here (blocked).
# After batch 1: out = {(30,300)}.
batch
+ sig 1 20 0
+ sig 0 30 300
+ sig 0 40 400
+ sig 1 40 0
end
# Batch 2 (the co-batch): all four F-A cases fire in ONE epoch.
#   case 1 (key 10): +pr(10,100) AND +blk(10)   -> out(10) net 0 (absent).
#   case 2 (key 20): +pr(20,200) AND -blk(20)   -> out(20,200) born (+1).
#   case 3 (key 30): -pr(30,300) AND +blk(30)   -> out(30,300) dies (-1).
#   case 4 (key 40): -pr(40,400) AND -blk(40)   -> out(40) net 0 (absent).
# After batch 2: out = {(20,200)}.
batch
+ sig 0 10 100
+ sig 1 10 0
+ sig 0 20 200
- sig 1 20 0
- sig 0 30 300
+ sig 1 30 0
- sig 0 40 400
- sig 1 40 0
end
